st short story ever written in Scots, provides a grotesque vision of the structures of an older Scotland. It is this older Scotland that Redgauntlet wishes to restore.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJacobitesvFiction. 0aPrinceszGreat BritainvFiction. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aHewitt, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWood, G A M, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107804750 cprintz978074860580440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074869861540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748698615423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748698615/original  a978-3-11-078047-5  Edinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK